49:36.808 --> 49:42.311
<i>Reciting poetry and prose</i>
<i>as the water lapped</i>
<i>our naked bodies</i>

49:42.313 --> 49:46.282
<i>It was a shared baptism
in a new life together.</i>

49:46.284 --> 49:50.286
<i>- After months of traveling...
- It's so cold.</i>

49:50.954 --> 49:52.688
<i>We found our paradise.</i>

49:52.690 --> 49:54.757
Bring me that dead resina.

49:55.659 --> 49:57.460
No.

49:57.462 --> 50:00.696
Leave that poor
suffering plant alone.

50:00.698 --> 50:02.465
I'll get you some firewood.

50:02.467 --> 50:04.533
Where did you get this?

50:04.535 --> 50:09.238
A surprisingly mean spirited ex,
sent it to me.

50:11.508 --> 50:15.011
"Vera,
Damn that Teddy
but he never fooled you.

50:15.013 --> 50:16.612
Best, George."

50:17.647 --> 50:19.215
Damn that George.

50:21.852 --> 50:24.587
Wait, you knew about Nena?

50:26.757 --> 50:32.261
I'm going to show you how
to make a perfect gin martini.

50:36.666 --> 50:40.669
I didn't break my toe dancing.

50:40.671 --> 50:47.143
You know, I got a call
from that damn reporter
about Nena's book

50:47.145 --> 50:52.615
Well, I pretended to know
all about it. Ho, ho, ho.

50:52.617 --> 50:57.420
And then after I hung up,
I kicked the pantry door in.

50:58.622 --> 51:02.825
Oh, I wonder
what happened
to that door.

51:05.562 --> 51:09.899
Theodore, moving.

51:09.901 --> 51:15.204
Writing, which is little nurse
made in dough.

51:16.106 --> 51:18.340
His idea of paradise.

51:19.743 --> 51:21.177
Yeah.

51:37.627 --> 51:40.129
♪

51:52.509 --> 51:54.477
Nikki, Nikki.

51:58.315 --> 52:03.285
Hey, Dora Theodora,
sit down, how are you?

52:03.287 --> 52:04.620
Good.

52:05.322 --> 52:07.690
I see you brought us stash.

52:08.558 --> 52:12.595
So, listen,
I've been thinking, uh...

52:12.597 --> 52:15.931
You sure your aunt
wants to do this?

52:15.933 --> 52:20.069
Hmm? Yeah, of course, she...
wants to share

52:20.071 --> 52:21.437
with the whole world.

52:22.772 --> 52:24.140
Okay.

52:24.142 --> 52:26.142
It's awfully brave of her.

52:26.144 --> 52:29.812
I'd want somebody
diggin' around my closet!

52:29.814 --> 52:31.580
It's a whole other story.

52:31.582 --> 52:34.416
But my friend told me
he would love to...

52:35.018 --> 52:37.653
get his hands on this, so...

52:37.655 --> 52:41.223
Wait, Nikki, you've to do
me a favor if you're gonna
take this.

52:41.791 --> 52:44.560
Okay, what's that?

52:44.562 --> 52:48.764
You've to come
to the Poetry Festival
next weekend.

52:49.766 --> 52:51.367
Fine, sign me up.

52:54.538 --> 52:55.638
The what?

53:17.127 --> 53:18.661
<i>Oh, yeah.</i>

53:18.663 --> 53:24.366
Yeah, I thought the
force majeure was
as fascinating as that...

53:29.706 --> 53:31.473
Yeah, hmm-mm.

53:32.676 --> 53:34.743
Okay, I gotta go, Mom.

53:35.812 --> 53:38.714
Yup, I love you too. Bye.

53:44.087 --> 53:46.655
Do depressions run
in our family?

53:47.757 --> 53:49.725
You are not depressed.

53:49.727 --> 53:53.729
You are unhappy,
if I were you,
I'd be unhappy too.

53:58.668 --> 54:01.270
Why are you going
to law school, Dora?

54:02.572 --> 54:03.706
Don't know.

54:04.307 --> 54:06.508
It will make my degree useful.

54:07.611 --> 54:09.645
There's one way to go, right?

54:09.647 --> 54:11.146
Go where?

54:11.148 --> 54:13.749
According to you, France.

54:13.751 --> 54:17.853
That is something that I say
when someone I know

54:17.855 --> 54:23.025
is about to commit themselves
to something that might <i>not</i> be
right for them.

54:23.027 --> 54:25.027
I was going
to secretarial school,

54:25.029 --> 54:27.863
instead I went to France.

54:27.865 --> 54:31.600
Oh, wow, right now,
I can't do anything,

54:31.602 --> 54:33.669
I can't go to France,
I can't go to Brazil,

54:33.671 --> 54:35.571
- I can't go anywhere.
- So, maybe

54:35.573 --> 54:37.840
I should just become a lawyer
so I can actually afford

54:37.842 --> 54:40.309
to do the things
that I wanna be doing,
Aunt Vera.

54:42.178 --> 54:44.246
You're a Wells, Dora.

54:44.248 --> 54:46.849
We do not follow
a straight line.

54:55.992 --> 54:57.760
Was dad like me?

55:02.065 --> 55:06.201
He... pursued his passions
mightily.

55:06.203 --> 55:08.937
So, no, you're not
like your dad.

55:09.806 --> 55:11.840
He was in the theater.

55:11.842 --> 55:15.311
When you came,
your mother wanted him to quit.

55:16.479 --> 55:20.549
I do know that he loved you
and your mom very much.

55:22.552 --> 55:24.420
She never talks about him.

55:33.096 --> 55:34.763
I think,
I will go in the village.

55:37.500 --> 55:39.435
If you need anything
just call me.

55:39.903 --> 55:41.870
I won't need you.

55:43.473 --> 55:45.174
But you do need me Aunt Vera

55:45.176 --> 55:49.378
because you have a broken toe
and I cannot wait
for it to be unbroken.

55:57.153 --> 55:58.921
I told you.

55:58.923 --> 56:03.625
I'm a pauper, I hold a big bag
of clothes I can't even afford.

56:10.066 --> 56:11.600
♪

56:21.711 --> 56:22.911
Abbey.

56:24.147 --> 56:25.714
I'm busy.

56:26.383 --> 56:28.584
I'm just returning the clothes.

56:29.886 --> 56:31.320
I didn't eat in them.

56:31.322 --> 56:34.857
Except when I ate my foot
at the music studio.

56:42.899 --> 56:44.733
Prosecco.

56:45.969 --> 56:48.637
Is that how you normally are?

56:48.639 --> 56:50.806
I mean, I admittedly
I don't know you that well

56:50.808 --> 56:54.009
but you got this weird look
in your face as if...

56:54.511 --> 56:56.412
nothing else mattered.

56:56.980 --> 56:59.515
You completely shut me down.

57:00.116 --> 57:02.117
- It was awful.
- I know, I know.

57:02.119 --> 57:03.986
I think it's my nerves.

57:03.988 --> 57:08.791
Um, my mom calls it,
"Leaving the planet."

57:09.659 --> 57:12.227
Yeah, I didn't mean
to do it at all.

57:12.229 --> 57:14.463
I'm, I'm so sorry.

57:16.466 --> 57:18.467
What's that about?

57:18.469 --> 57:21.036
Wow, I had a great idea.

57:21.038 --> 57:24.506
I think you should sing
at the Poetry Festival.

57:25.041 --> 57:26.875
That's a big event.

57:26.877 --> 57:28.710
You've got already
burnt me voice.

57:28.712 --> 57:32.347
Yeah, I know and that's,
that's once too many.

57:32.349 --> 57:37.886
Apparently, I'm in drastic need
of some emotional stylization
too.

57:43.393 --> 57:45.494
Cut that baby open.

57:45.995 --> 57:47.729
I need it.

57:48.364 --> 57:50.599
Why, what's going on?

57:50.601 --> 57:54.837
Oh, Dora, this is
the beginning
of the end.

57:54.839 --> 57:56.705
- It is?
- Yes.

57:56.707 --> 58:02.744
This is the first day
of the last 30 days
of my twenties.

58:04.414 --> 58:06.615
Oh, my God.

58:06.617 --> 58:10.352
I'm getting older, darling.

58:10.354 --> 58:12.654
- Shut up.
- Yes.

58:12.656 --> 58:15.824
I see like I'm just getting
wrinkly all over.

58:30.640 --> 58:32.508
Let's get out of here.

58:33.776 --> 58:36.979
And go where?
There's no where to go.

58:38.348 --> 58:41.950
Doesn't Saugerties have a...
lighthouse?

58:41.952 --> 58:45.854
Yeah, but it's like
way too cold
and windy.

58:49.893 --> 58:53.462
Oh, I know, you should like...

58:53.464 --> 58:55.697
we should go out there
and you should do some like

58:55.699 --> 58:58.267
performance out there
in honor of turning thirty.

58:58.269 --> 58:59.668
Like what?

59:05.508 --> 59:08.644
It's totally uncivilized
out here.

59:08.646 --> 59:10.946
This is awesome!

59:10.948 --> 59:13.448
- Be careful.
- Oh, my God.

59:13.450 --> 59:16.652
Okay, start picking up things
that we can like throw
into the river.

59:16.654 --> 59:18.220
It will just blow away.

59:18.222 --> 59:22.324
So, what, ? Just think of it is
like your life up until now

59:22.326 --> 59:23.392
And just blow them away.

59:23.394 --> 59:25.127
This is really depressing.

59:27.764 --> 59:30.132
Getting old is depressing.

59:30.767 --> 59:33.769
Let's go.

59:34.370 --> 59:36.004
Come on, you old, maid.

59:43.413 --> 59:45.113
Get more sticks.

59:47.250 --> 59:52.054
It's so pretty out here.

59:52.056 --> 59:55.223
It's such a cold day
to come out here.

59:56.426 --> 59:59.528
- Whoa!
- It's the light house.

59:59.530 --> 01:00:01.730
This is so cool.

01:00:10.807 --> 01:00:12.174
Ready?

01:00:24.420 --> 01:00:26.855
Farewell old days.

01:00:27.657 --> 01:00:30.792
Here's to better new ways.

01:00:32.829 --> 01:00:37.232
You're like a hawk, perched,
ready to devour.

01:00:38.334 --> 01:00:42.604
The Earth, the world, my heart
and all it's power.

01:00:42.606 --> 01:00:46.708
Thank you wind for listening.

01:00:47.176 --> 01:00:50.012
- Amen.
- Amen.

01:00:51.682 --> 01:00:54.883
Oh, that train is headed
to the city.

01:00:54.885 --> 01:00:57.886
- I wish we were on it.
- I know.

01:00:57.888 --> 01:01:01.923
Sometimes, I wish, I could
get on the through-way

01:01:01.925 --> 01:01:04.860
drive south and never come back.

01:01:06.262 --> 01:01:08.897
- Do it.
- I can't.

01:01:08.899 --> 01:01:11.833
I have to take care
of my step sister Tabatha...

01:01:12.268 --> 01:01:13.402
Right here.

01:01:18.474 --> 01:01:22.444
- Oh, what a cutie.
- Yes, she is cute.

01:01:22.446 --> 01:01:24.146
- And she is smart too.
- Yeah.

01:01:24.148 --> 01:01:28.684
Her parents, my dad
and his on-off, on-off,
girlfriend,

01:01:28.686 --> 01:01:31.787
they don't make the time
to take care of her.

01:01:32.422 --> 01:01:33.555
Oh, that's awful.

01:01:33.557 --> 01:01:36.725
Yes. So, otherwise,
I would be gone...

01:01:36.727 --> 01:01:38.794
long time ago.

01:01:38.796 --> 01:01:42.397
But you've your music, Abbey,
that's amazing, I mean,

01:01:43.366 --> 01:01:45.267
I don't have anything except...

01:01:46.836 --> 01:01:52.040
thoughts about being far away
and doing huge things.

01:01:52.042 --> 01:01:58.180
-Hmm.
-But, but how do I get
from here to there.

01:01:58.182 --> 01:02:01.416
You know, like I feel like
I'm in this...

01:02:01.418 --> 01:02:05.187
this old beige waiting room.

01:02:05.189 --> 01:02:06.521
Don't worry.

01:02:06.523 --> 01:02:08.890
Somewhere deal
will creep up on you

01:02:08.892 --> 01:02:12.027
and it might not be huge
but it fill massive.

01:02:12.029 --> 01:02:15.230
And the beige waiting room
will just be a memory.

01:02:23.873 --> 01:02:25.941
Hey, is that Nikki?

01:02:26.442 --> 01:02:27.743
Nikki?

01:02:30.246 --> 01:02:32.013
Whoa.

01:02:32.015 --> 01:02:34.182
What you doing here?

01:02:34.184 --> 01:02:35.684
This is so weird.

01:02:35.686 --> 01:02:37.285
Hey, well,
what are you doing here?

01:02:37.920 --> 01:02:40.388
We just made a sacrifice.

01:02:41.090 --> 01:02:42.591
Sacrifice?

01:02:42.593 --> 01:02:44.826
What kind of sacrifice?

01:02:44.828 --> 01:02:47.095
It is in honor
of Abbey's birthday.

01:02:47.097 --> 01:02:50.265
She's little upset
that she's turning 30.

01:02:50.267 --> 01:02:51.833
I mean, she's upset
because of, um,

01:02:51.835 --> 01:02:53.301
because of something else.

01:02:54.203 --> 01:02:55.570
Thirty?

01:02:55.572 --> 01:02:57.639
Oh, you poor little thing, you.

01:02:57.641 --> 01:03:01.076
In that case, you might just
throw yourself in the river
and get over with it.

01:03:02.078 --> 01:03:05.480
Thirty, believe me,
it doesn't matter.

01:03:06.682 --> 01:03:09.284
Least until you get
to be my age anyway.

01:03:10.853 --> 01:03:14.589
For instance, I just,
I just finished this record.

01:03:14.591 --> 01:03:17.025
- Everybody says it's great.
- Great.

01:03:17.027 --> 01:03:20.362
No, but see,
great is over rated.

01:03:20.863 --> 01:03:22.798
You know what I mean?

01:03:22.800 --> 01:03:25.333
Really, where's the life in it,
you know.

01:03:25.335 --> 01:03:30.005
I can't think the last time
that I made a record

01:03:30.007 --> 01:03:33.708
that had a track on it.
They had to...
grow on the listener.

01:03:33.710 --> 01:03:38.647
When you listen to a new thing,
something's not right,
but then you listen to it again.

01:03:38.649 --> 01:03:40.248
And again and again.

01:03:40.250 --> 01:03:44.119
And slowly but surely it grabs
and throws you in river.

01:03:45.922 --> 01:03:47.455
Now the Buddhists...

01:03:47.457 --> 01:03:51.326
Now Buddhists, the Buddhists
have a saying that,

01:03:51.328 --> 01:03:55.130
whatever you do
up until the age of 50,

01:03:55.132 --> 01:03:59.201
stop it and do something
completely different.

01:04:03.039 --> 01:04:05.440
Me, I'm little late on that one
myself but...

01:04:05.442 --> 01:04:09.010
But I thought you said
that age doesn't matter.

01:04:09.679 --> 01:04:11.313
It's true.

01:04:11.315 --> 01:04:13.748
I'm talking about the work
though, I mean,
if you're not sweat

01:04:13.750 --> 01:04:20.555
and working hard at something
then you're just not... living.

01:04:28.398 --> 01:04:32.434
On that note,
it's time for this one to go.

01:04:32.436 --> 01:04:36.905
- To go home.
- Oh, oh, Nikki, Nikki

01:04:36.907 --> 01:04:38.240
I'm all right.

01:04:45.648 --> 01:04:47.349
Hi, Aunt Vera.

01:04:49.051 --> 01:04:50.652
Went to the lighthouse.

01:04:59.095 --> 01:05:00.228
Vera?

01:05:07.303 --> 01:05:08.436
Vera?

01:05:15.845 --> 01:05:17.312
Vera?

01:05:20.883 --> 01:05:22.684
Aunt, Aunt Vera?

01:05:27.556 --> 01:05:29.057
Are you all right?

01:05:30.960 --> 01:05:33.028
How long you've been out here?

01:05:34.463 --> 01:05:35.997
I heard the train.

01:05:39.502 --> 01:05:41.102
This is nothing like it.

01:05:47.009 --> 01:05:49.044
Did you give him
the letters too?

01:05:49.412 --> 01:05:51.212
Well, mostly...

01:05:51.747 --> 01:05:53.248
scribbled thoughts.

01:05:54.250 --> 01:05:56.985
That's when Theo did
when he was gone.

01:06:00.623 --> 01:06:02.657
Once annually burned them.

01:06:04.994 --> 01:06:06.594
What's the use?

01:06:07.596 --> 01:06:09.431
I know 'em all by heart.

01:06:11.667 --> 01:06:13.134
Particularly one.

01:06:15.104 --> 01:06:18.640
"Dear Virginia.
How are you?

01:06:21.978 --> 01:06:23.645
I can't continue.

01:06:26.015 --> 01:06:30.185
And all the places
they would know, the people...

01:06:33.289 --> 01:06:34.456
the deadlines.

01:06:36.359 --> 01:06:37.492
Grab my hand.

01:06:38.561 --> 01:06:40.128
Like we used to.

01:06:40.496 --> 01:06:41.997
Jumping trains.

01:06:42.765 --> 01:06:45.500
And now, I'll pull you up.

01:06:48.137 --> 01:06:50.405
And we'll escape together."

01:06:54.910 --> 01:06:56.578
I don't have that letter.

01:07:02.051 --> 01:07:04.285
Because Theo never wrote it.

01:07:16.599 --> 01:07:18.400
You wanna travel, Dora.

01:07:19.635 --> 01:07:21.236
I'll give you the money.

01:07:22.938 --> 01:07:26.074
Okay, great.

01:07:26.076 --> 01:07:28.476
Because I don't want you
here anymore.

01:07:36.919 --> 01:07:40.755
Degraw is interested
in my journals.

01:07:46.262 --> 01:07:49.164
I wanted you to have
the spotlight, not...

01:07:49.166 --> 01:07:50.732
what's your name.

01:07:54.036 --> 01:07:57.772
What feeble half big brain,
do you posses?

01:07:57.774 --> 01:08:00.308
This says it's okay for you...

01:08:00.310 --> 01:08:04.145
to just serve up
my private moments on a platter

01:08:04.147 --> 01:08:06.281
to some complete stranger.

01:08:17.059 --> 01:08:19.394
You gave him the originals.

01:08:19.395 --> 01:08:23.531
For God Sake,
not even photo copies!

01:08:26.769 --> 01:08:27.868
Oh, God.

01:08:45.888 --> 01:08:48.256
♪

01:09:21.524 --> 01:09:23.158
Bye, Aunt Vera.

01:09:25.995 --> 01:09:28.263
<i>I know it was stupid, Mom.</i>

01:09:29.165 --> 01:09:30.932
My bus gets in at two.

01:09:33.335 --> 01:09:35.737
The test, what about the test?

01:09:37.273 --> 01:09:40.642
Yeah, I'll take it in Newark.
Bye.

01:09:58.928 --> 01:10:00.862
Please, get in, Dora.

01:10:10.639 --> 01:10:12.507
Oh, my God,
I'm feeling so sorry,

01:10:12.509 --> 01:10:14.943
like the way I treated you,
it was just no consideration

01:10:14.945 --> 01:10:18.746
for the other person.
I'm turning
into my mom. I mean...

01:10:18.748 --> 01:10:21.716
Oh, God, there's
no respect for you or anything

01:10:21.718 --> 01:10:26.554
and I'm so sorry, I'll call
The Graw and I'm sorry.

01:10:28.490 --> 01:10:30.225
Why do you have a trash can?

01:10:30.893 --> 01:10:32.293
What are these?

01:10:33.796 --> 01:10:35.563
Nothing, just...

01:10:36.465 --> 01:10:38.066
trash.

01:10:38.068 --> 01:10:39.767
What is they used to be?

01:10:41.270 --> 01:10:44.138
Some are, um...
images from my dreams

01:10:44.140 --> 01:10:49.744
and others are just thoughts...
it's junk, it's nothing,
it's just throw aways.

01:10:52.448 --> 01:10:56.618
Well, they may be a bit rough
but they are telling.

01:10:57.586 --> 01:11:00.355
A place where interesting
things occur.

01:11:00.357 --> 01:11:01.956
You know, my poetry club?

01:11:01.958 --> 01:11:03.558
Oh, no, I can't read these.

01:11:03.560 --> 01:11:05.059
Oh, not the way
they are right now,

01:11:05.061 --> 01:11:06.461
but you can work them.

01:11:06.463 --> 01:11:08.696
And read it at the festival.

01:11:09.898 --> 01:11:12.000
No way, no.

01:11:12.901 --> 01:11:14.669
If you read, I'll read.

01:11:41.997 --> 01:11:44.732
♪

01:11:56.078 --> 01:11:58.046
♪

01:12:23.405 --> 01:12:25.573
<i>Over and over...</i>

01:12:26.375 --> 01:12:28.343
<i>breaking the ice.</i>

01:12:29.878 --> 01:12:32.914
<i>Rocks, like blocks.</i>

01:12:34.683 --> 01:12:36.351
<i>Deep into mud.</i>

01:12:38.120 --> 01:12:41.089
<i>Thud.
Blood.</i>

01:12:42.758 --> 01:12:43.758
<i>Crud.</i>

01:12:47.129 --> 01:12:48.830
Enough with the rhyming.

01:12:49.531 --> 01:12:51.366
<i>How's the rhyme going?</i>

01:12:51.368 --> 01:12:55.103
Awful, um, I mean, I...

01:12:55.105 --> 01:12:59.207
I feel stuff, you know,
but it's not doing anything

01:12:59.209 --> 01:13:01.976
except just rolling
around inside me.

01:13:03.278 --> 01:13:05.680
You're in a muddle.

01:13:05.682 --> 01:13:09.250
It's a worst place
to be in everyday life but...

01:13:09.252 --> 01:13:11.753
best place to be for creativity.

01:13:13.021 --> 01:13:16.524
Listen, every writer that I know
including your grand uncle,

01:13:16.526 --> 01:13:18.960
every writer has trouble
writing.

